{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 09:11:06.209804", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary of network health\\n- The OSPF core/distribution/server-access fabric is stable. All FRR routers have full adjacencies and consistent routes for user subnets and the server farm.\\n- The server farm in 10.200.0.0/24 is reachable within its segment and from distribution/Core devices.\\n- Host_2_1_1_1 has normal end-to-end connectivity to DNS and web servers, including DNS resolution of web0.local.\\n- Host_1_1_1_1 cannot reach any destinations in 10.0.0.0/8 outside its local segment (including the DNS and web servers), resulting in DNS resolution and application failures on that host.\\n\\nDetected anomalies\\n- Host_1_1_1_1 has a misconfigured netmask: 10.1.1.2/8 instead of the expected /24, causing it to treat all 10.x.x.x targets as on-link and ARP for them, rather than sending to the default gateway.\\n- This misconfiguration leads to ARP failures and “Destination Host Unreachable” when contacting 10.200.0.0/24 (DNS/web), and name resolution failures for web0.local.\\n- A brief earlier “Destination Net Unreachable” from 10.2.1.1 to 10.200.0.2 was observed during initial testing from host_2_1_1_1, but subsequent tests show stable reachability; likely a transient condition during OSPF convergence.\\n\\nLocalization of the fault\\n- Fault localized to host_1_1_1_1 network interface configuration.\\n- Distribution/core/server-access routers and server farm appear healthy. OSPF adjacencies are Full, and routes are present and consistent.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Incorrect subnet mask on host_1_1_1_1: configured as 10.1.1.2/8 (255.0.0.0) instead of 10.1.1.2/24 (255.255.255.0).\\n- Consequence: host_1_1_1_1 ARPs for any 10.x address (including DNS 10.200.0.2 and web servers 10.200.0.3–.6) and never forwards to its default gateway 10.1.1.1, resulting in ARP INCOMPLETE/FAILED and connectivity loss to server farm and other 10.x networks.\\n\\nKey evidence\\n- Host addressing and routes:\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 ifconfig/ip: inet 10.1.1.2/8; ip route: default via 10.1.1.1; 10.0.0.0/8 dev eth0.\\n  - host_2_1_1_1 ifconfig/ip: inet 10.2.1.2/24; ip route: default via 10.2.1.1; 10.2.1.0/24 connected.\\n- Reachability/ARP from host_1_1_1_1:\\n  - Ping DNS/web from host_1_1_1_1: Destination Host Unreachable to 10.200.0.2 / 10.200.0.3.\\n  - ip neigh on host_1_1_1_1: 10.200.0.2 INCOMPLETE; 10.200.0.[3,4,6] FAILED; default gw 10.1.1.1 has lladdr but in DELAY state.\\n  - Ping to default gateway 10.1.1.1 succeeds; ping to off-subnet 172.16.0.7 (dist interface) succeeds, confirming L3 path OK when destination is not within 10.0.0.0/8.\\n- DNS setup on hosts:\\n  - /etc/resolv.conf on both hosts points to nameserver 10.200.0.2.\\n  - Curl from host_1_1_1_1 to http://web0.local shows ~4–5s timeouts (consistent with name resolution failure to 10.200.0.2).\\n  - Curl from host_2_1_1_1 to http://web0.local shows normal timing (name resolution and HTTP OK).\\n- OSPF/routing in infrastructure:\\n  - switch_dist_1_1, switch_dist_2_1, router_core_2, switch_server_access all show OSPF neighbors in Full state.\\n  - Routes:\\n    - switch_dist_1_1: C 10.1.1.0/24; O 10.200.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6.\\n    - switch_dist_2_1: C 10.2.1.0/24; O 10.200.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.8.\\n    - switch_server_access: C 10.200.0.0/24; O 10.1.1.0/24 and 10.2.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.10.\\n  - Pings from distribution to DNS (10.200.0.2) succeed with low latency.\\n  - Host_2_1_1_1 to DNS/web pings succeed consistently.\\n\\nImpact assessment\\n- Host_1_1_1_1 cannot resolve or reach any services in 10.200.0.0/24 (DNS/web), and more broadly cannot reach any remote 10.x networks due to on-link misclassification caused by the /8 mask.\\n- Other hosts and infrastructure are not impacted; overall network routing and server farm services are healthy., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} 